text: The Wiyabal (also Widjabal, possibly from confusion of the letter in the older spelling Wijabal) were an indigenous Australian people of the state of New South Wales. ==Country== Norman Tindale assigned the Widyabal about of territory on the Upper Richmond River, running south from Kyogle to the area in the vicinity of Casino, with their eastern limits at Dunoon. ==Alternative names== * Ettrick tribe * Noowidal * Nowgyjul * Waibra * Watchee * Watji Source: ==Some words== * groomon/kroomon (kangaroo) * kooning (mother) * marmong (father) * tobury (tame dog) * tucki (whiteman) Source: ==Notes== ===Citations=== ==Sources== * * * * * * * Category:Aboriginal peoples of New South Wales
title: Wiyabal
